AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE
Blog Gen Instruction: This section is your primary creative brief. Use this audience data to inform every paragraph, every sentence, every word choice. You are writing for this specific person with this specific intent. Satisfy them completely.
Intent-Specific Audience Profile:

Who They Are: Primarily 18–28, self-identified alt or goth-adjacent, some "goth-curious" from mainstream audiences. Mix of absolute beginners and people with basic nail skills (can apply solid colour, can't do art). Mostly doing nails at home — no professional tools, no UV lamp in many cases.
What They Want From This Post: An actual step-by-step they can follow tonight with what they already own or can buy cheaply. Not a mood board. Not a "here are 20 goth nail ideas" listicle. They want to know: what do I buy, what do I do first, and what do I do when it goes wrong.
What Satisfies Them: Specificity. Knowing which brush size. Knowing which top coat dries matte without pilling. Knowing they can do something that looks decent even on short nails. A tutorial that doesn't assume they have a nail tech's toolkit.
What Frustrates Them: Tutorials that show a beautifully finished result without real process steps. Vague instructions like "add nail art." No acknowledgment that black polish is harder to apply than light polish. No help when things go wrong (bubbles, streaks, smudging).

Top 5 Pain Points:

Black polish goes streaky or patchy — doesn't know why or how to fix it
Fine detail work (spiderwebs, lace lines) looks messy because they're using the wrong brush or tool
Chrome or metallic effects don't work on regular polish — only on gel, and they don't know why
Matte top coat either pills or goes glossy after a day — brand and technique unknown
Designs that look great on long coffin nails don't work on their short nails — no adaptation advice given

User Sentiment: Eager but slightly intimidated — they love the aesthetic deeply and want to own it with their hands, but feel like the good results are gated behind expensive tools or professional skill.
